  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "I'm calling the hardhat-etherscan task programmatically as part of a contract deployment. Since etherscan takes some time to index the new contract I added a retry logic to wait some seconds and call the verify task a couple of times until it successfully verifies the contract.\r\nEvery time I call the verify task, it recompiles the contracts and display the output in the console making it difficult to follow my deployment logs.\r\n\r\nIt would be great to have a flag to avoid compiling the contracts when calling the verify subtask programmatically",
